						<summary>

						<p>This registers a gift of 12 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> by one Śāvāndi Tiruvaraṅga Nārāyaṇaṉ Bhāskaradēvaṉ of Tiruppalāttuṟai for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Mahādēva at the place. Tiruppalāttuṟai is said to have formed part of Uttamaśīlichaturvēdimaṅgalam a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> on the southern bank (of the Kāvērī).</p>						

						</summary>
